doc_summary_long: An average of nine firearms a day were confiscated at US airports last year - most of them loaded - according to figures released by the Transportation Security Administration (TSA). The agency, which has become an unlikely hit on Instagram, discovered a total 3,391 guns on travellers in 2016, 83 per cent of which, it said, were loaded.
doc_summary_short: An average of nine firearms a day were confiscated at US airports last year - most of them loaded - according to figures released by the Transportation Security Administration (TSA).
doc_title: Record number of guns intercepted at US airports last year
